'''奥贝格费尔诉霍奇斯案'''（{{lang-en|''Obergefell v. Hodges''}}，{{scite|576|644|2015}}）是[[美国联邦最高法院|美国联邦最高法院]]对于[[美国同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]的重要判例。最高法院在判决中称同性婚姻的权利受到[[美国宪法|宪法]]保障，各州不得立法禁止。

2015年1月16日，最高法院决定将该案与[[田纳西州|田纳西州]]的坦科诉哈斯拉姆案（''Tanco v. Haslam''）、[[密歇根州|密歇根州]]的德波尔诉斯奈德案（''DeBoer v. Snyder''）以及[[肯塔基州|肯塔基州]]的伯克诉贝希尔案（''Bourke v. Beshear''）这三宗同性婚姻案件一同合并审理。同年4月28日，最高法院就该案进行了口头辩论。<ref>{{cite web|author=Singh, Tejinder|title=“Super-cuts” from same-sex marriage arguments|url=http://www.scotusblog.com/2015/04/super-cuts-from-same-sex-marriage-arguments/|publisher=[[SCOTUSblog|SCOTUSblog]]|date=April 28, 2015|access-date=2015-06-26|archive-date=2021-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303092305/https://www.scotusblog.com/2015/04/super-cuts-from-same-sex-marriage-arguments/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Gerstein, Josh|title=The 8 most awkward moments in the Supreme Court’s gay-marriage arguments|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2015/04/supreme-court-gay-marriage-arguments-awkward-moments-117444.html|newspaper=[[Politico|Politico]]|date=April 28, 2015|accessdate=2015-06-26|archive-date=2015-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150825041540/http://www.politico.com/story/2015/04/supreme-court-gay-marriage-arguments-awkward-moments-117444.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>6月26日，最高法院最终以5比4作出判决，认定根据[[美利坚合众国宪法第十四条修正案|宪法第十四修正案]]的条款，各州必须为申请结婚的同性伴侣颁发-{}-结婚证，并承认由其他州所颁发的同性结婚证。大法官[[安东尼·肯尼迪|安东尼·肯尼迪]]撰写了[[多数意见书|多数意见书]]，并得到了[[鲁斯·巴德·金斯伯格|鲁斯·巴德·金斯伯格]]、[[史蒂芬·布雷耶|史蒂芬·布雷耶]]、[[索尼娅·索托马约尔|索尼娅·索托马约尔]]、[[艾蕾娜·卡根|艾蕾娜·卡根]]四位大法官的认同。反对该判决的则有首席大法官[[约翰·罗伯茨|约翰·罗伯茨]]以及大法官[[安东宁·斯卡利亚|安东宁·斯卡利亚]]、[[克拉伦斯·托马斯|克拉伦斯·托马斯]]和[[塞缪尔·阿利托|塞缪尔·阿利托]]。<ref name="SC-20150626">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Obergefell, et al. v. Hodges, Directory, Ohio Department of Health, et al. |url=http://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/14pdf/14-556_3204.pdf |format=[[PDF|PDF]] |date=2015年6月26日 |work=[[美國最高法院|美國最高法院]] |accessdate=2015年6月29日 |archive-date=2015年6月26日 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626145937/http://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/14pdf/14-556_3204.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20150626">{{cite news |last=Liptak |first=Adam |title=Same-Sex Marriage Is a Right, Supreme Court Rules, 5-4 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/27/us/supreme-court-same-sex-marriage.html |date=June 26, 2015 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=June 26, 2015 |archive-date=2015-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626152024/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/27/us/supreme-court-same-sex-marriage.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>大法官安東尼·甘迺迪撰寫的判決書中引用了中國儒學經典著作《大戴禮記》中的《[[:wikisource:大戴禮記/哀公問於孔子|哀公問於孔子]]》中孔子所講述的一句話：「禮者，政之本與！」<ref name="SC-20150626"/>

2022年6月24日，最高法院以5比4的表決推翻了[[羅訴韋德案|羅訴韋德案]]的判決後，大法官[[克拉倫斯·托馬斯|托馬斯]]表示將會重新審議本案、[[格里斯沃爾德訴康乃狄克州案|格里斯沃爾德訴康乃狄克州案]]及[[劳伦斯诉德克萨斯州案|勞倫斯訴德克薩斯州案]]。<ref>{{Cite web |title=高院裁決恐引發連鎖反應 同性婚姻等裁決或被推翻 |url=https://www.singtaousa.com/4142427 |website=www.singtaousa.com |language=zh |access-date=2022-06-26}}</ref>

==背景==
===訴訟===
2013年7月19日，來自[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[辛辛那提_(俄亥俄州)|辛辛那提]]的同性伴侶於[[美国俄亥俄南区联邦地区法院|美国俄亥俄南区联邦地区法院]]提出奥贝格费尔訴卡西奇案（{{Lang|en|Obergefell v. Kasich}}，其中卡西奇為當時俄亥俄州第69任州長[[约翰·卡西奇|约翰·卡西奇]]），指稱該州歧視已於其他州合法結婚的同性伴侶。伴侣中的一方约翰·阿瑟罹患[[肌萎缩性脊髓侧索硬化症|肌萎缩性脊髓侧索硬化症]]（渐冻人症），已经处于[[绝症|末期]]，因此这对伴侣希望俄亥俄州政府在他的[[死亡证明|死亡证明]]上将另一位伴侣詹姆斯·奥贝格费尔列为他的未亡配偶，因为这对伴侣已经在2013年6月11日于[[马里兰州同性婚姻|马里兰州合法结婚]]。俄亥俄州户籍登记处认为歧视已婚同性伴侣属于违宪，但俄亥俄州总检察长办公室则宣布要坚持俄亥俄州的同性婚姻禁令。<ref>{{cite news|last=Hastings|first=Deborah|title=Terminally ill Ohio gay man gets dying wish, marries partner after being flown to another state|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/terminally-ill-gay-man-ohio-flies-partner-maryland-tarmac-wedding-article-1.1399228|accessdate=July 21, 2013|newspaper=New York Daily News|date=July 15, 2013|archive-date=2019-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212234516/https://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/terminally-ill-gay-man-ohio-flies-partner-maryland-tarmac-wedding-article-1.1399228|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wvxu.org/post/cincinnati-lawsuit-challenges-ohios-same-sex-marriage-ban|title=Cincinnati lawsuit challenges Ohio's same-sex marriage ban|date=July 19, 2013|publisher=WVXU|accessdate=July 21, 2013|archive-date=2013-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002140646/http://wvxu.org/post/cincinnati-lawsuit-challenges-ohios-same-sex-marriage-ban|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Zimmerman, Julie|title=To get married, they left Ohio|url=http://www.cincinnati.com/article/20130714/NEWS10/307140009/To-get-married-they-left-Ohio|newspaper=[[The_Cincinnati_Enquirer|The Cincinnati Enquirer]]|date=July 14, 2013|accessdate=2015-06-27|archive-date=2015-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923203726/http://www.cincinnati.com/article/20130714/NEWS10/307140009/To-get-married-they-left-Ohio|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Geidner, Chris|title=Two Years After His Husband’s Death, Jim Obergefell Is Still Fighting For The Right To Be Married|url=http://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/his-huband-died-in-2013-but-jim-obergefell-is-still-fighting|newspaper=BuzzFeed News|date=March 22, 2015|accessdate=2015-06-27|archive-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626082840/https://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/his-huband-died-in-2013-but-jim-obergefell-is-still-fighting|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===地方法院判决===
2013年7月22日，地方法官蒂默西·S·布莱克通过了这对伴侣的请求，{{link-en|暂行法令|interim order|暂时限制}}俄亥俄州户籍登记处处理当地死亡证明，直至登记处将约翰·阿瑟列为「已婚」、詹姆斯·奥贝格费尔列为他的「未亡配偶」为止。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/ohio-officials-ordered-to-recognize-gay-couples-marriage |title=Ohio Officials Ordered To Recognize Gay Couple's Marriage |accessdate=July 22, 2013 |newspaper=Buzzfeed |date=July 22, 2013 |archive-date=2018-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626082848/https://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/ohio-officials-ordered-to-recognize-gay-couples-marriage |dead-url=no }}</ref> 蒂默西·S·布莱克在法令中写道：「历史上，俄亥俄州的法律一直很明确：在俄亥俄州外完婚的婚姻，只要在完婚处有效，那么在俄亥俄州也有效」，他还表示近亲或未成年人间的婚姻虽然在俄亥俄州违法，但如果在其它管辖地区判为合法，是会受到俄亥俄州承认的。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://s3.documentcloud.org/documents/738510/obergefell-v-kasich-order.pdf|title=Order Granting Plaintiffs' Motion for a Temporary Restraining Order|date=July 22, 2013|publisher=''Obergefell v. Kasich'', Docket 1:13-cv-00501-TSB, U.S. So. Dist. Ohio (2013)|accessdate=2015-07-05|archive-date=2020-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201011012412/http://s3.documentcloud.org/documents/738510/obergefell-v-kasich-order.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> 俄亥俄州总检察长[[麦克·迪怀恩|麦克·迪怀恩]]表示他不会就此法令上诉。<ref>{{cite news |last=Geidner |first=Chris |title=Ohio Attorney General Has No Plans To Appeal Temporary Restraining Order In Gay Couple’s Case |url=http://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/ohio-attorney-general-has-no-plans-to-appeal-temporary-restr |accessdate=July 26, 2013 |newspaper=BuzzFeed |date=July 25, 2013 |archive-date=2018-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626082816/https://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/ohio-attorney-general-has-no-plans-to-appeal-temporary-restr |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2013年8月13日，蒂默西·S·布莱克将暂行限制令延期至2013年12月底，并将[[禁制令|禁令救济]]的口头辩论安排于2013年12月18日。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.edgeboston.com/index.php?ch=news&sc=&sc2=news&sc3=&id=148121|title=Gay Ohio Couple Win Extension Recognizing Marriage|date=August 13, 2013|publisher=Edge Boston|accessdate=2015-07-05|archive-date=2015-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923233844/http://www.edgeboston.com/index.php?ch=news&sc=&sc2=news&sc3=&id=148121|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2013年9月25日，蒂默西·S·布莱克根据原告方的请求，更换被告（原来是俄亥俄州州长及总检察长）为俄亥俄州卫生部主任，案名也随之变为「奥贝格费尔诉威姆斯洛案」（{{lang-en|''Obergefell v. Wymyslo''}}）。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/09/25/ohio-gay-marriage-lawsuit_n_3989740.html|title=Ohio Gay Marriage Lawsuit Seeking Death Certificate Recognition To Include Similarly Situated Couples|date=September 25, 2013|publisher=Huffington Post|accessdate=2015-07-05|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924192106/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/09/25/ohio-gay-marriage-lawsuit_n_3989740.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2013年10月22日，原告约翰·阿瑟去世。被告方请求以无实际意义为由驳回此案。蒂默西·S·布莱克法官于2013年11月1日的法令中，拒绝了驳回请求。<ref>{{cite book|title=Order Denying the Motion to Dismiss|publisher=''Obergefell v. Wymyslo'', 1:2013-cv-00501-TSB, U.S. So. Dist. Ohio (2013) |url=http://docs.justia.com/cases/federal/district-courts/ohio/ohsdce/1:2013cv00501/164617/54/0.pdf}}</ref> 2013年12月23日，蒂默西·S·布莱克法官裁定，俄亥俄州拒绝承认其他管辖地区的同性婚姻属于歧视，并命令俄亥俄州在死亡证明上承认这一同性婚姻。他写道：「一个州终止其他管辖地区完婚的婚姻，即是侵犯了私人婚姻关系、家庭关系等受到最高法院保护的亲密关系。」<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/govbeat/wp/2013/12/23/ohios-ban-on-gay-marriage-ruled-unconstitutional-in-limited-case/ | last1=Bzdek | first1=Vincent | title=Ohio's ban on gay marriage ruled unconstitutional in limited case | work=Washington Post | date=December 23, 2013 | accessdate=January 17, 2014 | last2=Sewell | first2=Dan | archive-date=2020-12-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201217224904/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/govbeat/wp/2013/12/23/ohios-ban-on-gay-marriage-ruled-unconstitutional-in-limited-case/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Declaratory Judgment and Permanent Injunction, December 23, 2013|url=http://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=12839958848055482717& |publisher=Google Scholar|accessdate=October 6, 2014}}</ref>

另一桩案件「亨利诉威姆斯洛案」（{{lang-en|''Henry v. Wymyslo''}}）与奥贝格费尔案同时由蒂默西·S·布莱克法官受理。2014年2月10日，亨利案中，四对于其它州合法结婚的同性伴侣提出上诉，要求州政府将伴侣双方都列于孩子的出生证明上。其中三对伴侣是住在俄亥俄州的女性，都预计于2014年下半年迎来宝宝的降生。第四对伴侣是住在纽约的男性，领养了一个2013年出生于俄亥俄州的儿子。<ref>{{cite news|last=Myers|first=Amanda Lee|title=Couples Sue to Force Ohio's Hand on Gay Marriage|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/couples-sue-force-ohios-hand-gay-marriage-22443699|accessdate=February 11, 2014|newspaper=ABC News|date=February 10, 2014|archive-date=2014-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223232039/http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/couples-sue-force-ohios-hand-gay-marriage-22443699|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在诉讼待决期间，原告方修正诉讼为「请求法院宣布俄亥俄州的同性婚姻禁令违宪」。为给俄亥俄州提出上诉留出准备时间，蒂默西·S·布莱克法官于2014年4月4日宣布，他将在4月14日颁布法令要求俄亥俄州承认其他地区的同性婚姻。<ref>{{cite news|last=The Associated Press|title=Judge to strike down Ohio ban on recognizing gay marriage|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/04/04/ohio-gay-marriage/7304753/#|accessdate=April 4, 2014|newspaper=USA Today|date=April 4, 2014|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128015542/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/04/04/ohio-gay-marriage/7304753/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=NPR>{{cite news |last=Memmott |first=Mark |title=Federal Judge Says He'll Strike Down Ohio's Same-Sex Marriage Ban |url=http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2014/04/04/299072507/federal-judge-says-hell-strike-down-ohios-same-sex-marriage-ban |accessdate=April 4, 2014 |newspaper=National Public Radio (NPR) |date=April 4, 2014 |archive-date=2015-04-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150425091336/http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2014/04/04/299072507/federal-judge-says-hell-strike-down-ohios-same-sex-marriage-ban |dead-url=no }}</ref>主要被告俄亥俄州卫生部主任泰德·威姆斯洛辞职后，由于与案件无关的原因，兰斯·海姆斯出任卫生部临时主任，「亨利诉威姆斯洛案」更名为「亨利诉海姆斯案」（{{lang-en|''Henry v. Himes''}}）。<ref>{{cite news|last=Vardon|first=Joe|title=Department of Health director leaving Kasich administration|url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2014/02/04/department-of-health-director-leaving-kasich-administration.html|accessdate=April 12, 2014|newspaper=The Columbus Dispatch|date=February 5, 2014|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919012449/https://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2014/02/04/department-of-health-director-leaving-kasich-administration.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2014年4月14日，蒂默西·S·布莱克法官裁定，俄亥俄州必须承认其他地区的同性婚姻，<ref name="April 14 gay marriage">{{cite news|last=Myers|first=Amanda Lee|title=Judge: Ohio must recognize other states' gay marriages|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/04/14/ohio-gay-marriage-court/7691313/|accessdate=April 14, 2014|newspaper=USA Today|date=April 14, 2014|archive-date=2020-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107050143/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/04/14/ohio-gay-marriage-court/7691313/|dead-url=no}}</ref>4月16日，除了原告方请求的出生证明外，延缓判决执行。<ref name="April 16 gay marriage">{{cite news|newspaper=Metro Weekly|date=April 16, 2014|accessdate=April 16, 2014|title=Federal judge grants partial stay in Ohio marriage-ban ruling|url=http://www.metroweekly.com/2014/04/federal-judge-grants-partial-stay-in-ohio-marriage-ban-ruling/|first=Justin|last=Snow|archive-date=2014-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525200500/http://www.metroweekly.com/2014/04/federal-judge-grants-partial-stay-in-ohio-marriage-ban-ruling/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==法院意見書==
